   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Conserve Budaka Environment for 70,000 in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Conserve Environment Project in Budaka Uganda intends to promote tree planting, energy saving and reduce the indiscriminate destruction of trees, misuse of natural resources. Key among issues affecting communities is food and water shortage resulting from harsh climatic conditions, environmental degradation like increased soil erosion, prolonged droughts, food insecurity due to low crop yields, scarcity of water, loss of biodiversity, loss of water catchment areas and loss of employment.</narrative>
  </description>
